sentence: Looking at units outstanding versus one week prior within the universe of ETFs covered at ETF Channel, the biggest outflow was seen in the iShares MSCI Eurozone ETF ( EZU ), where 8,500,000 units were destroyed, or a 3.2% decrease week over week.
Among the largest underlying components of EZU, in morning trading today NXP Semiconductors ( NXPI ) is down about 0.5%, and Aercap Holdings ( AER ) is lower by about 1.1%.

And on a percentage change basis, the ETF with the biggest outflow was the ProShares Ultra Consumer Goods ( UGE ), which lost 100,000 of its units, representing a 22.2% decline in outstanding units compared to the week prior.
Among the largest underlying components of UGE, in morning trading today Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) is trading flat, and Coca-Cola Company (KO) is higher by about 0.1%.
